    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You twist the elemental properties of a spell, breath weapon, or other effect utilizing elemental energies to shift from its current element into another. The creature causing the triggering spell or effect (such as a red dragon’s Fire Breath, an ankheg’s Acid Spray, a kraken’s Lightning Storm, the <em>@UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.RpKjTlYASrfqUPVA]{cone of cold}</em> spell, or similar) must succeed on a Charisma saving throw or the damage the effect deals changes to one of the following damage types of your choice: acid, cold, fire, lightning, or thunder.<br>Content licensed under the @UUID[Compendium.koboldpressogl.koboldpressjournal.JournalEntry.KoboldPressOGL00.JournalEntryPage.KoboldPressOGLpg]{Open Game License}",
